id: pm-gg8e
title: Sentry tracesSampleRate is hardcoded at 0.2 — expose as configurable knob or document intent
description: "Sentry is initialized with tracesSampleRate: 0.2 (instrument.ts:227). This rate is not configurable via settings or env var, and is not documented anywhere. At 20% sampling, 80% of CLI command spans are dropped. For a low-volume developer CLI this may be appropriate, but if the install base grows or performance debugging requires full-trace coverage, there is no operational lever. The value should either be documented as intentional (with the reasoning) or wired to a SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE env var following Sentry SDK conventions."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 4
tags[2]: "area:observability","area:sentry"
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:05:12.734Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-19T15:33:07.262Z"
author: audit-observability-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- Either: (A) tracesSampleRate reads from SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE env var with 0.2 as the default; the env var is listed in the telemetry env-var docs (pm-r7md); OR (B) a code comment at instrument.ts:227 explains the rationale and documents that the value is intentionally static for this use case.\n- Whichever option, no behavior change for existing installs."
parent: pm-5oj5
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "Wired tracesSampleRate to SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE via resolveTracesSampleRate() (default 0.2, honours [0,1], falls back on invalid/out-of-range). Documented Sentry env vars in docs/CONFIGURATION.md."
expected_result: Operators can tune or disable Sentry performance tracing without code changes; default behaviour unchanged.
actual_result: "SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE now controls the rate (0=off, 1=full); unset/invalid keeps 0.2. Coverage 100/100/100/100, docs updated."
