  src/core/sentry/instrument.ts,project,"Add resolveTracesSampleRate() reading SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE (default 0.2, clamped to [0,1])"
  tests/unit/core/sentry/sentry-helpers.spec.ts,project,resolveTracesSampleRate branch coverage + init wiring assertion
close_reason: "Wired tracesSampleRate to SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE via resolveTracesSampleRate() (default 0.2, honours [0,1], falls back on invalid/out-of-range). Documented Sentry env vars in docs/CONFIGURATION.md."
body: "## Context\n\nFile: src/core/sentry/instrument.ts:227 — `tracesSampleRate: 0.2` hardcoded in SentryModule.init.\n\nThe Sentry SDK supports SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE env var natively. There is no existing override path in the pm-cli initialization code.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Either: (A) tracesSampleRate reads from SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE env var with 0.2 as the default; the env var is listed in the telemetry env-var docs (pm-r7md); OR (B) a code comment at instrument.ts:227 explains the rationale and documents that the value is intentionally static for this use case.\n- Whichever option, no behavior change for existing installs.\n\n## Evidence\n\nsrc/core/sentry/instrument.ts:227 — hardcoded 0.2."
